Data availability

            All data used in this study are available online. The hourly total water content of soil layer, near-surface air temperature and precipitation from the ERA5-Land reanalysis dataset are publicly available at the CDS website from 1981 to 2020 (cds.climate.copernicus.eu/datasets/reanalysis-era5-land?tab=overview) (ref. 51). The 3-hourly total water content of soil layer, near-surface air temperature and precipitation from the GLDAS-Noah reanalysis dataset are publicly available at the GES DISC website from 1981 to 2020 (https://disc.gsfc.nasa.gov/datasets/GLDAS_NOAH025_3H_2.1/summary and https://disc.gsfc.nasa.gov/datasets/GLDAS_NOAH025_3H_2.0/summary). The 3-hourly total water content of soil layer, near-surface air temperature and precipitation from the CRA-Land reanalysis dataset are publicly available at the China Meteorological Data Service Centre website from 1981 to 2020 (https://data.cma.cn/data/cdcdetail/dataCode/NAFP_CRA40_FTM_3HOR_GRB.html). The daily root-zone soil moisture and surface soil moisture from the GLEAM dataset are publicly available from 1981 to 2020 (https://www.gleam.eu/). The daily surface soil moisture from the ESA-CCI dataset is publicly available from 1981 to 2020 (https://www.esa-landcover-cci.org/). The ground-based observed soil moisture from OzNet is publicly available (http://www.oznet.org.au/). The ground-based observed soil moisture from ISMN is publicly available (https://ismn.earth/en/). The LAI from GLOBMAP dataset is publicly available via Zenodo at https://doi.org/10.5281/ZENODO.4700264 (ref. 65). The USDM drought severity maps are publicly available (http://droughtmonitor.unl.edu). The daily total water content of soil layer, near-surface air temperature, precipitation and LAI from CMIP6 are publicly available at the ESGF website (https://aims2.llnl.gov/search). The land use and land cover from MCD12C1 are publicly available at the Land Processes Distributed Active Archive Center website (https://lpdaac.usgs.gov/products/mcd12c1v061/). The precipitation data from the GSWP-3 are available via DIAS at https://doi.org/10.20783/DIAS.501 (ref. 66). The data necessary to reproduce the main results are available via Zenodo at https://doi.org/10.5281/ZENODO.13624543 (ref. 67).
          Code availability

            Analysis and figure generation were performed using Python (v.3.12.2) and R (v.4.2.0). The computer code necessary to reproduce the main results is available via Zenodo at https://doi.org/10.5281/ZENODO.13624543 (ref. 67).
